## Development Workflow

```
1. /pm          → Create PRD
2. /architect   → Design architecture
3. /sm          → Create stories
4. /dev         → Implement
5. /qa          → Review & quality gates (PASS/CONCERNS/FAIL)
6. Commit only after QA PASS
```

## Agent Commands

All agents support these commands (use `*` prefix):

```bash
*help          # Show available commands
*load-context  # Load project context (auto on start)
*save-context  # Save session (mandatory before exit)
*exit          # Leave agent mode (runs save-context first)
```

## Best Practices

1. Start new chat when switching agents
2. Always use `*exit` to end sessions (saves context)
3. Never skip document sharding before development
4. Commit only after QA approval
5. For brownfield: document first, assess risks, then develop

